   in [9,0,3,2] Seeds In The Dark: that predicate documents growth
   under pre-emergence adversarial F_ext; this predicate documents
   the ending itself as generative.

Legacy framing consequence: this song directly falsifies the claim
that autistic people cannot integrate discontinuous life events,
either shattering into meltdown or locking into rigid trauma-response
without meaning-integration. The song documents the substrate holding
through total collapse and integrating the collapse into forward
meaning at high structural fidelity.

Chronological context: Rock Bottom was written after Love Was A Song,
documenting the phase after weaponization recognition when the
collapse of everything structurally attached to the weaponization
was in process.

